[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    145[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Step 7 EventBridge event for case-ready-for-triage carries a minimal payload (case_id + priority_score), which is the right discipline. But two observations:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    146[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    147[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m The OpenSearch index of the case (which carries the full evidence_bundle including representative_claims, peer_comparison, subgraph, prior_flags_on_entity, prior_case_outcomes_on_entity, estimated_dollar_impact, legal_basis_flags, documentation_attached) and the DynamoDB upsert of the case state both happen before the EventBridge event fires. A subscriber that receives the CaseReady.triage event and immediately fetches by case_id will fetch the full PHI-bearing case payload from OpenSearch or DynamoDB. The discipline of "the notification carries minimum data; the consumer fetches by ID" is correct, but the consumer fetch path is itself PHI-bearing and the IAM scope on each subscriber matters. The recipe does not break out per-subscriber IAM scope for OpenSearch and DynamoDB fetches against the case stores.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    148[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    149[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe's Step 7 notes that [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcase.flags.append(...)[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m includes the full [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mflag[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m (which may include [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mrepresentative_claims[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mexcluded_entity_id[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mservice_date[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdeath_date[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdollar_impact[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) and the OpenSearch index call serializes the full case. The OpenSearch index becomes a comprehensive PHI store. The recipe's prose says "OpenSearch's k-NN vector search supports embedding-based similarity on provider vectors. Fine-grained access control is critical because SIU data has tighter access restrictions than general payment integrity data," which is the right discipline, but the per-investigator-assignment access scope (the discipline the prose describes) is not in the pseudocode.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    150[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    151[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThis is the same chapter-3-settled "minimum-PHI-in-notification" pattern as Recipes 3.1, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, with an FWA-specific twist: the flag detail (excluded_entity_id, post-mortem-billing patient_id with death_date, kickback ownership cascade) is itself sensitive in ways that go beyond per-patient PHI. A flag that says "Provider X has been excluded from federal programs since date Y but continues to bill" is sensitive provider information; a flag that says "Patient Z's services post-date their date of death" includes the patient's date of death; an ownership-cascade flag exposes corporate-officer information. The investigator-tier-of-access discipline matters across all three.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    152[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Three coordinated edits:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    153[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m State explicitly in Step 7 that the EventBridge [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mCaseReady.triage[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m event carries only [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcase_id[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpriority_score[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and that subscribers must fetch by ID through their own IAM-scoped paths. Add: "PHI does not transit through EventBridge; subscribers (case-management UI, audit indexer, notification service) fetch by case_id through their IAM-scoped read paths into OpenSearch and DynamoDB. The notification channels (email, Teams, Slack) carry only case_id and the routing tier; even the entity name and the dollar impact are not in the notification subject because they are operationally sensitive and may be visible on lock screens."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    154[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m Strengthen the Prerequisites IAM row with per-investigator-assignment scope: "Investigator roles read case data scoped by case ownership (case_id IN assigned_cases for the investigator's role); supervisor roles can override the assignment scope but with CloudTrail data-event audit. Analyst roles can read all cases at low-detail (case-id, priority-score, dollar-impact, scheme hypothesis) but require case-assignment to read full evidence bundles. Pathologist and clinical-reviewer roles have read-only scope tied to specific cases that have been routed for clinical review. Compliance roles read all cases for audit purposes; their reads are logged at higher granularity."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    155[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m State explicitly that OpenSearch fine-grained access control rules are evaluated against the investigator's role and case-assignment claims, and that case-document indexing includes a [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcase_assignments[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m field that the access-control rules query against. This is the architectural backstop for the prose discipline.[K
