[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    161[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" Fairness, bias, and equity monitoring bullet ("Detection rates by specialty, by geography, by patient demographics, by provider race/ethnicity when identifiable, by practice setting... Mitigations include case-mix adjustment, subgroup performance review, and threshold-tuning review specifically for equity").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    162[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe is unusually clear about subgroup dimensions: provider race/ethnicity (when identifiable), patient demographics, geography, practice setting (safety net, rural, FQHC). Naming these explicitly is the right discipline. But the architectural artifacts that make subgroup monitoring binding rather than aspirational are not specified: where the demographic and provider-attribute store lives, who has read access, how it joins to flag events and case outcomes, what the audit trail for subgroup queries looks like, what IAM scope the QuickSight dashboard role and the retraining job role need on demographic data, and how the dashboard avoids exposing row-level demographic data to dashboard viewers.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    163[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    164[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mProvider race/ethnicity data is unusually sensitive in the FWA context because the historical pattern of disproportionate enforcement against minority-owned practices is a well-documented concern. Some state laws restrict secondary use of demographic data more tightly than HIPAA restricts PHI per se. The recipe's framing-level treatment is correct; the architectural backstop that operationalizes it is missing.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    165[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    166[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe case-mix adjustment is itself a methodological-and-data-architecture concern: it requires patient-level acuity, comorbidity, and demographic data joined to provider attribution, which is a substantial subgroup-attribute-rich data flow that needs governance. Same finding shape as Recipes 3.2 S2, 3.3 S2, 3.4 S2, 3.5 S2 (now five recipes deep).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    167[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a "Subgroup data access" paragraph or row to Prerequisites: "Subgroup performance and detection-rate monitoring requires read access to provider attributes (race, ethnicity when identifiable, geography, practice setting) and patient demographic attributes (age band, sex, race, ethnicity, insurance type, language). These attributes may be governed differently from clinical PHI in some regulatory regimes (state laws often restrict secondary use of race/ethnicity data); restrict read access to the demographic-and-attribute stores to the retraining job role and the fairness-monitoring dashboard role, and audit subgroup queries via CloudTrail data events. The QuickSight dashboard backed by Athena should query an aggregated subgroup-metrics table (flag rate by provider specialty by geography by practice setting; case-disposition rates by patient demographic; overpayment-recovery rates by provider attribute), not the raw demographic-joined flag archive, so that dashboard-user access does not require row-level read on the subgroup attributes. Case-mix adjustment requires patient-level demographic data joined to provider attribution; this join occurs in a controlled environment with output limited to aggregated metrics." Strengthen the IAM row with the per-role scope: retraining job role gets [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mglue:GetTable[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:GetObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m only on the demographic-joined view; fairness-monitoring dashboard role gets read-only on the aggregated subgroup-metrics table.[K
