[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    174[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies that SIU operations under legal privilege have implications for data architecture. But the specific infrastructure primitives that operationalize the privilege boundary are not specified: separate AWS account in an Organization Unit governed by general counsel; separate VPC with no peering to general analytics environments; separate KMS keys controlled by GC-administered roles with key-policy allow lists that exclude general analytics roles; distinct CloudTrail trail with delivery to a GC-controlled S3 bucket; distinct OpenSearch domain and DynamoDB tables for case data with explicit IAM-and-data-classification labels; SCP-level controls preventing data export from the privileged-environment account. The general consequence of getting these primitives wrong is that work product may lose privilege protection during litigation discovery, which is the exact risk the legal-privilege architecture is meant to prevent.[K
