[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    196[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The case state DynamoDB table and the OpenSearch case index are read by multiple roles (investigator UI, analyst triage, audit, case-management API). The fwa-flags EventBridge bus is written by the rules-engine Lambda, the statistical detector SageMaker Processing job, the graph-analytics SageMaker Processing job, and the supervised re-ranker SageMaker hosted endpoint, and is read by the evidence-aggregator Lambda and the audit indexer. The recipe gives generic least-privilege framing in the IAM row but doesn't break out per-consumer roles for these shared resources. For an FWA system whose flag outputs feed compliance-mandated regulatory referrals and whose case data is potentially privileged, the blast-radius minimization matters: a compromised role with broad case-write access could silently corrupt case state or flag history, which would propagate into wrong investigator routing, wrong dollar-impact estimates, and wrong case dispositions.[K
