[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    203[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Why-These-Services Amazon Kinesis paragraph ("Real-time claim and eligibility feeds (from clearinghouses or EDI gateways) flow through streaming"); Architecture Diagram ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mA[Claims feed\n837/835/270/271] --> B[Amazon Kinesis\nclaims-stream][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m); Prerequisites table.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    204[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Clearinghouse-to-payer EDI feeds (837 claims, 835 remittance, 270/271 eligibility) are typically authenticated and encrypted via SOAP/MIME EDIINT (AS2), HTTPS POST with HMAC, or SFTP with PGP encryption. The recipe describes the Kinesis ingress at a high level but doesn't specify the clearinghouse-side authentication and encryption protocol, the AWS-side ingress endpoint (API Gateway with mutual TLS, or AWS PrivateLink to a VPC-private endpoint, or Direct Connect), or the trading-partner agreement (TPA) discipline that governs the EDI relationship. The 837 claim file format itself contains PHI (patient SSN-ish identifiers, diagnosis codes, service dates); the ingress channel needs to be HIPAA-compliant end-to-end with documented TPAs that are part of the BAA discipline. Same finding shape as Recipe 3.4 S3 (HL7 v2 ingress) and Recipe 3.5 S4 (MLLP bridge).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    205[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a clearinghouse-ingress note to the Why-These-Services Kinesis paragraph: "The clearinghouse-to-AWS ingress is the PHI surface for the largest single data flow in this architecture. Authentication and encryption: AS2 (EDIINT) for clearinghouse-grade interoperability; HTTPS with mutual TLS as the modern alternative; SFTP with PGP file-level encryption for batch file transfer. AWS-side ingress endpoint: API Gateway with mutual TLS authentication, or AWS PrivateLink to a VPC-private endpoint, or Direct Connect for the largest-volume relationships. The trading partner agreement (TPA) with the clearinghouse is part of the BAA discipline; the BAA covers the AWS-side handling and the TPA covers the clearinghouse-to-payer handoff. CloudTrail data events on every PutObject in the inbound staging bucket; Kinesis SSE with customer-managed KMS keys; the ingress Lambda runs in a VPC with no public egress." Add to Prerequisites a Clearinghouse-Ingress row that names the TPA and AS2/mutual-TLS posture.[K
