[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    219[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Architecture Diagram ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mD[Provider data\nNPPES / PECOS / LEIE / SAM] --> E[AWS Transfer Family\n+ AWS Glue][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mF[External: Sunshine Act\nstate filings / death master] --> E[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m); Why-These-Services AWS Transfer Family is named in the Ingredients table but does not have a dedicated paragraph.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    220[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m External data sources (NPPES, PECOS, LEIE, SAM, Sunshine Act, state filings, death master, commercial vendors like LexisNexis or Thomson Reuters CLEAR) push data through SFTP, HTTPS, or specific vendor-defined protocols. AWS Transfer Family supports SFTP, FTPS, and AS2 with KMS encryption at rest, but the recipe doesn't specify whether Transfer Family endpoints are public or VPC-private, the authentication method (SSH key for service-account access, password with IAM mapping, custom identity provider), or source-IP allowlists for known external-source egress ranges. Death-master files are PHI-adjacent; the LEIE list is public but the time-correlation between LEIE date and post-exclusion claim activity is sensitive operational intelligence. Same shape as Recipe 3.5 S6.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    221[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add an AWS Transfer Family note to the Why-These-Services section: "AWS Transfer Family for external data feeds (NPPES, LEIE, Sunshine Act, state filings, death master, commercial vendor data). Use a VPC endpoint (not public) for Transfer Family in production; restrict source IPs to known external-source egress ranges via security group rules or IAM-resource-policy conditions; authenticate via SSH key with the source providing the public key out of band, rotated per the source's key-rotation policy; encrypt at rest with customer-managed KMS keys; CloudTrail data events on every PutObject and GetObject on the external-data inbound prefix." Add to Prerequisites a row covering external-data ingress posture.[K
