[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    394[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" Model monitoring and drift detection bullet ("The supervised re-ranker, the Isolation Forests, and the GNN embeddings all drift. Detectors that worked last quarter degrade because the underlying distribution shifts (new providers, new coverage policies, changed patient mix). Drift monitoring must be part of the production infrastructure: distribution shift on features, prediction drift on model outputs, and labeled-outcome drift on confirmed cases.").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    395[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies drift as a core operational concern and correctly names three drift types (feature distribution shift, prediction drift, labeled-outcome drift). But the architectural primitives are not specified: where the baseline distributions are stored, how drift is detected (KS test, PSI, Wasserstein distance), what action is taken on drift (alarm to MLE on-call, automatic threshold adjustment, model retraining trigger), what cadence drift is evaluated. SageMaker Model Monitor is named in the AWS service list but not in this specific context; the relationship between SageMaker Model Monitor and the drift-detection discipline is not made explicit in either the architecture diagram or the Why-These-Services section.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    396[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    397[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mFor Recipe 3.6 specifically, drift on the supervised re-ranker has direct case-routing consequences: a re-ranker whose scoring distribution has shifted will rank cases differently from how it ranked them at training time, and cases that should be at the top of the queue will land in the middle. Because investigator throughput is the binding capacity constraint (3-8 cases per investigator per month per the benchmarks), drift-induced ranking errors directly reduce the recovery-per-investigator-month rate.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    398[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Either (a) add a paragraph to the General Architecture Pattern's Retraining and rule tuning subsection explicitly naming the drift-detection primitives, or (b) update the AWS Implementation Why-These-Services section to add a SageMaker Model Monitor paragraph: "SageMaker Model Monitor for the supervised re-ranker, the Isolation Forest, and the GNN embedding similarity index. Baseline distributions captured at training time; daily monitoring jobs compute distribution-shift metrics (PSI for tabular features, KS test for prediction-score distributions, Wasserstein distance for embedding-space drift); CloudWatch alarms on threshold breaches notify the MLE on-call; threshold breaches trigger investigation rather than automatic action because drift may be legitimate (a new payer line of business, a new specialty in the panel) or adversarial (a scheme that has shifted to evade detection)."[K
