[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    456[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mFor an SIU environment that may end up under federal subpoena, network-level audit is the complement to API-level audit. CloudTrail records "who called the API" but doesn't record "which IP addresses talked to which IP addresses inside the VPC." Investigators reconstructing access patterns to case data (was there an exfiltration attempt? was an investigator's account compromised?) need both layers. Same recurring chapter-wide finding as Recipes 3.2 N2, 3.3 N2, 3.4 N2, 3.5 N2.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    457[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add to the VPC row or to the CloudTrail row: "VPC Flow Logs enabled on the VPC carrying Lambda, SageMaker, OpenSearch, Neptune, and AppSync traffic; logs delivered to a dedicated S3 bucket with KMS encryption and retention aligned to the deepest applicable retention requirement (FCA statute-of-limitations considerations can extend FWA-investigation log retention to ten years or longer; criminal case logs may be retained indefinitely under specific programs)."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    458[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    459[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mFinding N3: Clean Rooms Cross-Payer Governance Specifics Underspecified[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    460[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    461[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSeverity:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m LOW[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    462[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mExpert:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Networking / Compliance[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    463[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Why-These-Services AWS Clean Rooms paragraph; Variations Cross-payer intelligence sharing extension; "Where it struggles" "Cross-payer schemes" bullet.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    464[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies AWS Clean Rooms as the enabling infrastructure for multi-payer intelligence sharing, and correctly notes that "the governance work around it is the harder part." But the specific Clean Rooms-side governance disciplines that production multi-payer collaborations require are not named: Collaboration creation with explicit member roles, Clean Rooms analysis rules (aggregation rules with minimum aggregation thresholds, list rules for permitted joins, custom rules for specific analytic patterns), differential privacy parameters where applicable, the contributing-payer's data-prep responsibilities (data residency, PHI redaction beyond what Clean Rooms enforces), and the audit trail of Clean Rooms queries. For an FWA collaboration where the analytic results may inform regulatory referrals, the Clean Rooms query log is itself part of the evidence chain.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    465[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a paragraph to the Variations Cross-payer intelligence sharing extension: "Clean Rooms-specific governance includes: Collaboration creation with explicit member roles; analysis rules at the table level (aggregation rules with minimum aggregation thresholds; list rules for permitted joins; custom rules for specific patterns); differential privacy parameters where applicable; contributing-payer data-prep including data residency, PHI redaction beyond Clean Rooms enforcement, and HIPAA-aligned data classification; an audit trail of Clean Rooms queries that becomes part of the evidence chain when analytic outputs inform regulatory referrals. The cross-payer collaboration agreement is upstream of the Clean Rooms infrastructure: Healthcare Fraud Prevention Partnership (HFPP) participation is a common precondition; some collaborations also require state regulatory pre-approval. Coordinate with legal counsel and compliance before configuring the Clean Rooms collaboration."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    466[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    467[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mVoice Reviewer[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    468[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    469[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhat's Done Well[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    470[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    471[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe opening Monday-morning SIU vignette is publication-ready voice. The whiteboard, the network diagram, the three clinics in the same strip mall, the four providers from the same training cohort, the two DME suppliers with overlapping ownership, the toxicology lab with 80% of the referrals, the $11.7M paid total, the average $29k per patient versus $3.2k peer norm, the six months of investigation, the analyst who "got curious about why one lab kept showing up in the referral data," and the closing line "how many other whiteboards should we be drawing right now that we haven't even started" lands the operational reality of organized scheme detection in two paragraphs without any rhetorical excess. This is the densest scheme-detection framing in any cookbook recipe.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    472[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The fraud/waste/abuse terminology disambiguation is precise and operationally useful. The framing that "most real cases are mixtures" along the spectrum (a provider who started with waste, drifted into abuse, eventually into fraud) is exactly how senior SIU practitioners describe the problem.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    473[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The "the pain here is different from every other recipe in this chapter" framing followed by six substantive bullets (stakes are enormous, adversary is adaptive and organized, false-positive cost is high, true-positive discovery is rare, workflow is multi-party and partially legal, rules encode law and contract) is the right pedagogical scoping. Each bullet ties to a specific FWA-domain concern that distinguishes the problem from other anomaly detection problems.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    474[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The scheme taxonomy is the strongest single teaching anchor. Phantom billing, upcoding, unbundling, medically unnecessary services, kickbacks and self-referral, identity theft and credential abuse, collusive networks, patient-side abuse, billing-mill patterns: each is one to two paragraphs with operational detection clues that match what every senior SIU analyst would describe. The legal grounding (42 USC 1320a-7b for Anti-Kickback, 42 USC 1395nn for Stark, etc.) is unusually substantive.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    475[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Rules-Versus-Models subsection is the right pedagogical reframe and the closing posture ("the right answer is 'both, and in specific places'") is operationally correct.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    476[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Statistical and ML Methods That Fit subsection is the broadest method survey in any chapter-3 recipe (eleven methods with one to two paragraphs each), and the realistic-progression posture at the end ("start with rules plus statistical baselining plus a first pass at graph features. Add Isolation Forest once enough data exists. Add supervised re-ranking once labels accumulate. Add GNN embeddings as the program matures. Don't try to build all layers at once") is the kind of operations-engineer voice the cookbook is built on.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    477[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Graph-Is-The-Secret-Sauce subsection is the recipe's biggest pedagogical contribution. The framing of the graph as the differentiating capability between mature and immature programs, combined with the explicit "the highest-dollar cases, the organized schemes, the ones that pay for the program three times over, are almost all relational" in The Honest Take, is the design lesson most first-time builders miss.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    478[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Data Requirements and the Unglamorous Work subsection's "60% of the first year on data foundation and 40% on detection logic, and the teams that invert that ratio produce more alerts but not more cases" framing is the most candid program-design framing in any cookbook recipe.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    479[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Alert Fatigue Has a Different Flavor Here subsection correctly distinguishes FWA alert fatigue from clinical alert fatigue, and the four design implications (prioritization not optional, dollar impact drives priority, evidence bundling is the unit of work, feedback loops must be structurally honest, suppression rules politically sensitive) are concrete and operationally actionable.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    480[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Regulatory and Legal Context subsection is the most legally grounded treatment in any cookbook recipe. Each subsection (legal privilege, referral obligations, FCA exposure, HIPAA and Privacy Act, state-specific laws, retention) names a specific statutory or regulatory anchor.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    481[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Honest Take is publication-ready voice. The eleven lessons (graph differentiates mature programs; investigators produce work, not the model; rules engine underappreciated; peer group definition is ongoing; labels are worth fighting for; legal relationship matters more; LLM-assisted documentation review is genuinely useful with caveats; flag rate as primary metric is the trap; adversarial evolution is faster than expected; build case management before the third detector; the politics) are each substantive paragraphs that would each justify their own subsection in a standard treatment.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    482[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The closing trap warning ("flag rate as the primary metric") is publication-ready voice on the most consequential business-metrics framing in this domain. The "Educate leadership accordingly" close is the kind of operations-engineer-talking-to-leadership posture the cookbook does well.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    483[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Variations and Extensions section covers the right adjacent patterns at substantive depth and explicitly cross-references related recipes (3.1 duplicate detection; 3.3 billing code anomalies; 3.4 medication dispensing; 3.5 lab outliers; 3.9 EHR access; 5.x entity resolution; 8.x NLP; 13.x knowledge graphs; 2.x LLM/Generative AI). The cross-references are operationally accurate.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    484[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Style hygiene is exceptionally clean: zero em dashes verified directly, no marketing language, no documentation-voice. The 70/30 vendor balance is preserved cleanly.[K
