[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    499[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The performance benchmarks table presents specific ranges that read as published or measured numbers. The table's HTML-comment TODO acknowledges they are directional from typical payment integrity project experience and references NHCAA and the Healthcare Fraud Prevention Partnership for benchmark sources. Two specific numbers warrant additional caveat regardless of whether the table is replaced: the "Catch rate on confirmed fraud (recall, retrospective)" claim implies a measured retrospective ground truth that most SIU programs do not have systematically (the labeled-outcomes problem the recipe correctly identifies elsewhere); the "Estimated recoverable dollars per case" range varies enormously by scheme type and program maturity, and a single range across all configurations may be misleading.[K
