[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    525[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Either (a) replace the sample NPIs with NPIs that pass Luhn-check (e.g., generate a valid synthetic NPI using the CMS NPPES Luhn algorithm), or (b) replace with a placeholder ("[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m<valid-NPI>[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m") with an HTML-comment disclaimer ("Sample NPIs are placeholders; production output carries Luhn-validated NPIs from NPPES."). Option (a) is the smaller editorial change; option (b) is more honest about the synthetic nature.[K
