[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    541[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Variations and Extensions "LLM-native investigation assistance" extension ("Beyond documentation review, LLMs can assist across the investigation lifecycle: drafting subpoena language based on case facts, suggesting relevant prior OIG enforcement actions, producing investigator-ready narrative summaries of cases, querying the graph in natural language ('show me all entities within three hops of this provider that received payments over $50,000 in the last year'). The investigator becomes a supervisor of AI-generated drafts rather than a from-scratch author. Requires careful prompt engineering, grounding, and human review.").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    542[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The extension correctly identifies the productivity-tool framing ("the investigator becomes a supervisor of AI-generated drafts rather than a from-scratch author") and the closing-discipline ("careful prompt engineering, grounding, and human review"). But two specific FWA-domain concerns are not named: (1) drafting subpoena language using LLM-generated text raises bar-association considerations because subpoena-drafting may constitute legal practice; the LLM output should be a draft for a licensed attorney rather than a final document, and the validation discipline is more stringent than the documentation-review LLM-assist pattern. (2) "Querying the graph in natural language" introduces the risk that the LLM produces a Gremlin or SPARQL query that doesn't match the investigator's intent; the production pattern is to surface the generated query for investigator review before execution rather than executing directly.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    543[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expand the extension paragraph to name the FWA-specific validation disciplines: "Drafting subpoena language with LLM assistance is an attorney-supervised activity; the LLM produces a draft for a licensed attorney to review and finalize, not a document for direct submission. Querying the graph in natural language requires surfacing the generated Gremlin or SPARQL query for investigator review and approval before execution; LLMs can produce syntactically valid queries that don't match the investigator's intent, and a query that returns the wrong subgraph is itself an investigative artifact that needs explanation. The investigator-supervisor pattern applies across all of these uses; the LLM is a productivity tool, not a decision-maker."[K
