[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    620[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m A2 [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m MEDIUM [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m Architecture [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m Architecture Diagram (no DLQs configured); Prerequisites table; "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" disaster-recovery paragraph [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m No Dead Letter Queue or [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mOnFailure[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m destination configured for the stream-normalizer, rules-engine, evidence-aggregator, or outcome-capture Lambdas. For an FWA system whose flag outputs feed compliance-mandated regulatory referrals, a dropped event in the rules-engine path is a missed flag on a critical-rule violation (post-mortem billing, billing-by-excluded-entity); a dropped event in the evidence-aggregator is a case that never gets built; a dropped outcome event is a case-disposition that never gets recorded for FCA-exposure documentation. Fix: add [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mstream-normalizer-dlq[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mrules-engine-dlq[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevidence-aggregator-dlq[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140moutcome-capture-dlq[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m SQS queues with [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mOnFailure[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m destinations; CloudWatch alarms on DLQ depth (alarm threshold 1 for stream-normalizer because a single dropped claim is an unscored claim); replay older than the regulatory-referral compliance window escalates to compliance-team review rather than auto-replay. [38;2;192;197;206m|[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    621[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m A3 [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m MEDIUM [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m Architecture / Healthcare Compliance [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" Provider appeals and due-process workflows bullet; Step 7 case-bundle construction; Step 9 outcome-event taxonomy [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m Recipe correctly identifies in prose that providers have due-process rights and that case management must support appeals (record requests, appeals tracking, reversals feeding back to detection), but Step 9's ten outcome states have no appeal-stage, no immutable evidence-as-of-decision snapshot, no appeal-outcome state taxonomy (appeal_upheld / appeal_overturned / appeal_modified / appeal_withdrawn), and no feedback path from appeal-overturned outcomes to the detection logic. A reader who builds from the pseudocode produces a system without due-process backstops, which is the exact failure mode the prose warns against. Fix: add appeal-stage states, immutable evidence-as-of-decision snapshots in [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcase.evidence_history[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, appeal-outcome taxonomy, false_positive_post_appeal label flow back to the supervised classifier, provider record-request handling. Alternatively (smaller fix): explicit deferral note in Step 9 with cross-link to the Why This Isn't Production-Ready bullet. [38;2;192;197;206m|[K
