[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    674[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThere are zero HIGH findings. The MEDIUM findings cluster across architectural completeness with both prose-vs-pseudocode asymmetry signature (A3 appeals workflow, A4 reference-data versioning) and graph-construction internal inconsistency signature (S1). A1 (idempotency), A2 (DLQs), S2 (PHI minimization), S3 (subgroup governance), S4 (legal privilege primitives) are the recurring chapter-wide and recipe-distinctive patterns. The LOW findings cover operational and editorial polish.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    675[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    676[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe two highest-leverage fixes are S1 (graph-construction inconsistency) and A3 (provider appeals workflow). S1 is editorially substantive but the corrected pseudocode supports the high-value queries the prose describes; without the fix, the recipe's biggest pedagogical contribution (graph-as-secret-sauce) is undermined by the canonical example. A3 is editorially smaller (an appeal-state-machine deferral note plus an evidence-history-snapshot discipline) but is materially important because adverse actions overturned through inadequate due process are the FCA-exposure risk the prose correctly identifies.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    677[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    678[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A1 is the now-recurring trigger-idempotency pattern, surfacing for the twelfth consecutive recipe (2.4-2.10 and 3.1-3.6). The cookbook would benefit substantially from a shared appendix that covers the patterns once. Each subsequent recipe could reference the appendix rather than repeat the discipline. With the per-recipe-edit posture producing diminishing returns, the trigger-idempotency appendix is the highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    679[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    680[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A2 (DLQs) is operationally critical for Recipe 3.6 specifically because flag outputs feed compliance-mandated regulatory referrals under 42 CFR 422.504(h) and 438.608. The DLQ-depth alarm threshold for the stream-normalizer path should be 1 (single-event sensitivity), not the typical "alert on sustained backlog" pattern.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    681[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    682[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S2 is the now-recurring PHI-minimization-inside-the-BAA pattern with the seventh distinct surface across the cookbook (Chapter 2 prompts; Recipe 3.1 examiner reasoning; Recipe 3.2 patient-facing reminders for high-stigma specialties; Recipe 3.3 SNS notification payload; Recipe 3.4 SNS interrupt-alert with high-stigma drug class; Recipe 3.5 SNS critical-callback with high-stigma test class; Recipe 3.6 case-ready triage with provider-and-flag-detail sensitivity including post-mortem-billing dates and ownership-cascade corporate-officer information). A cookbook-wide PHI-minimization appendix would consolidate all seven surfaces with one teaching pass.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    683[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    684[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S3 is the five-recipe chapter-wide subgroup-governance pattern (Recipes 3.2, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6 all flag the same shape). Treat the subgroup-governance appendix as the second-highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment alongside trigger-idempotency.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    685[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    686[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S4 is unique to Recipe 3.6 in the chapter (legal-privilege architecture is an SIU-distinctive concern). The fix gives the architect infrastructure primitives to bring to the GC conversation rather than leaving the architect with no specific proposals.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    687[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    688[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Honest Take section is publication-ready and should be preserved verbatim. The eleven-paragraph structure (graph differentiates mature programs; investigators produce work, not the model; rules engine underappreciated; peer group definition is ongoing; labels are worth fighting for; legal relationship matters more; LLM-assisted documentation review is genuinely useful with caveats; flag rate as primary metric is the trap; adversarial evolution is faster than expected; build case management before the third detector; politics involve compliance/legal/ops/tech; moral tension of accusing people sometimes wrongly) is the kind of operations-engineer voice the cookbook is built on. The closing observation that "the temptation to over-automate (let the model decide who gets audited) is real and it's wrong" is the kind of moral-clarity framing that distinguishes the cookbook from documentation.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    689[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    690[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Monday-morning SIU vignette is the densest scheme-detection framing in any cookbook recipe and should not be shortened. The whiteboard, the network diagram, the specific dollar amounts ($11.7M paid, ~400 patients, $29k average vs $3.2k peer norm), the six months of investigation that "emerged from a tip from a former employee, a pattern in the urine toxicology claims, an FBI request, and an analyst who got curious," and the closing line "how many other whiteboards should we be drawing right now that we haven't even started" are publication-ready voice.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    691[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    692[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe scheme taxonomy (phantom billing, upcoding, unbundling, medically unnecessary services, kickbacks and self-referral, identity theft and credential abuse, collusive networks, patient-side abuse, billing-mill patterns) is the strongest single teaching anchor in any chapter-3 recipe and should be preserved verbatim. The specific operational detection clues for each scheme type match what every senior SIU analyst would describe.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    693[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    694[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Graph-Is-The-Secret-Sauce subsection is the recipe's biggest pedagogical contribution. The framing of the graph as the differentiating capability between mature and immature programs, combined with The Honest Take's reinforcement that "the highest-dollar cases, the organized schemes, the ones that pay for the program three times over, are almost all relational," is the design lesson most first-time builders miss. The S1 fix preserves this teaching by making the canonical pseudocode example actually demonstrate the architecture the prose describes.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    695[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    696[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Regulatory and Legal Context subsection is the most legally grounded treatment in any cookbook recipe to date. Each specific statutory anchor (42 USC 1320a-7b for Anti-Kickback, 42 USC 1395nn for Stark, 31 USC 3729-3733 for FCA, 42 CFR 422.504(h) and 438.608 for Medicare Advantage and Medicaid managed care fraud reporting, 45 CFR 164.512(f) for HIPAA disclosures to law enforcement) is operationally accurate and is the kind of detail-level grounding that distinguishes the cookbook from documentation.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    697[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    698[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mStyle hygiene is exceptionally clean: zero em dashes (verified directly), no marketing language, no documentation-voice. The 70/30 vendor balance is preserved cleanly. HTML-comment TODO discipline is correct (eight TODOs total, all forward-placeholder, no bracket-style visible TODOs). The NHCAA/CMS loss estimates, SIU ROI benchmarks, and HIPAA-eligible Bedrock model list TODOs should be resolved before publication; the forward-looking GNN, aws-samples, performance benchmarks, federated-learning, and AWS blog post placeholders read cleanly.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    699[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    700[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mCoordinate with the existing code review ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mreviews/chapter03.06-code-review.md[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m). The code review FAILed on one ERROR (float-to-Decimal at the case_record evidence_summary write) and five WARNINGs. ERROR is recipe-3.6-Python-companion-only and is a critical fix. WARNING 1 (OWNERSHIP_CASCADE detector cannot fire because organization nodes are not created) parallels this expert review's S1 finding (the main recipe pseudocode also has the missing-vertex problem; harmonize the two). WARNING 3 (patient node ID is the raw patient_id rather than a hash in the Python companion) is the Python-companion side of S1's privacy concern; the recipes should harmonize. WARNING 4 (S3 put_object with [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mServerSideEncryption="aws:kms"[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m without [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mSSEKMSKeyId[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) parallels Recipes 3.1, 3.2, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5. WARNING 5 ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140maggregate_flags_to_cases[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m ConditionExpression with fresh uuid.uuid4() on every call) is the Python-companion analog of A1; the trigger-idempotency appendix should harmonize across the main pseudocode and the Python companion.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    701[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    702[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe risk profile is comparable to Recipes 3.4 and 3.5 in autoverification-gating consequence terms and elevated relative to those in legal-and-regulatory consequence terms. The recipe's prose addresses the elevated risk correctly; the operational-completeness backstops (DLQs, idempotency, appeals workflow, reference-versioning propagation, suppression expiry, drift monitoring, rule change management, legal-privilege primitives, subgroup governance) are the right next-pass priorities. With those addressed, Recipe 3.6 sits at the same publication-ready quality bar as the strongest Chapter 2 and Chapter 3 recipes.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    703[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    704[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe fairness surface area is unusually substantive: provider race/ethnicity is itself a subgroup dimension, and the recipe correctly names the historical pattern of disproportionate enforcement in FWA contexts. Case-mix adjustment is the right mitigation but requires patient-level demographic data joined to provider attribution that needs governance (S3). The framing-level treatment is the best in any recipe; the architectural backstop is the operational-completeness gap.[K
